- The string parameter `path` is an absolute path starting with a slash `'/'`.
- The string result is the simplified canonical path.
- The canonical path starts with a single slash `'/'`.
- Any two directories in the canonical path are separated by a single slash `'/'`.
- The canonical path does not end with a trailing `'/'`.
- The canonical path only contains directories on the path from the root directory to the target file or directory, excluding periods `'.'` or double periods `'..'`.
- Multiple consecutive slashes in the canonical path are replaced by a single slash.